      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARMOUR FORCE (2) has returned to racing in good order. Opened with a near miss this track and trip and then stepped up to this distance and delivered this grade in a tight finish. He will have taken further improvement, and carrying just a half kilo more, he can go on with the job. COLOURS OF AUTUMN (7) progressed nicely last time out to score by 0.7 lengths in a CL3 over 1250m at this track. Has a low barrier and tumbles in weight at this level. That brings her right into it. CHOIR BOY (3) resumed here over shorter and went close, before dropping right out in the AF race. He's better than that, and third-up can show more. PEROVIC (4) is a well-performed galloper who will come into his own over longer trips. Will be doing his best work late.",
